      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense as a high-level summary, but I need to dig deeper into the more \"raw\" arguments they'll bring up. If I'm in the room and an executive argues that race-conscious hiring is actually a way of \"lowering the bar\" because they assume certain groups naturally lack the same competitive edge or educational foundation as others, how should I respond? Basically, can you elaborate on the argument that meritocracy is the only way to ensure we aren't just prioritizing identity over actual capability? I need to know how they'll frame the idea that race is a reliable proxy for difference in skill or intelligence.",
